sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K180010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Composite part, consisting of BBa_K180011 and BBa_K180012, but with BBa_K180011 reading along reverse strand, and BBa_K180012 reading along the forward strand.
Forms the 'rock' primary plasmid in Team:Southampton's rock-paper-scissors project design.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Richard Wilson, Stephanie Chambers
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: See relevant biobrick component parts (BBa_K180011 and BBa_K180012).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part has been specified as a basic BioBrick, due to some of the component parts reading in reverse (unable to specify using the component BioBrick format).
